title: Simunye Airfield
content:
Simunye Airfield (ICAO: FDSM) is an airstrip serving Simunye, a town in the Lubombo Region of Eswatini.

The marked runway has a 150 metres (492 ft) unpaved overrun on the northeast end.

The Sikhuphe VOR-DME (Ident: VSK) is located 15.9 nautical miles (29.4 km) southwest of the airstrip.[4]
